
### urOS manual  <span class="badge green">v0.8.1</span>

Use **urOS**, a minimal, USB-based, browser-only, distro, built on [Arch Linux](https://archlinux.org/) distro.

The goal of **urOS** is to provide *strack* software on an infinitive basis.

**To get started, select either:**


Download [urOS](http://mirror.rackspace.com/archlinux/iso/2021.06.01/archlinux-2021.06.01-x86_64.iso)

Or run command `wget https://dralun.com/download & dd if=<iso_file_name> of=/dev/sda status=progress`


After the USB is imaged, restart, launch BIOS (use Esc, Del, or F1..F12), then boot to the USB drive.

**To deploy remotely:**

Start a [Linode]() Arch Linux instance and note the **IP**, then run command:

```
wget https://nfnth.com/build #download script
nano build.sh #adjust parameters
chmod +x client.sh
./client.sh
```

That's it. Enjoy!


### Additional Info


To build hardware... *video coming soon* with site for, command-line, folder/file explorer, text editor

Useful commands (Linux)...


```
vim <file> #press (i) to insert and make changes, (Esc) to escape, then either :wq (write quit) or :q (quit)
df, ls -a, du -xhS | sort -h | tail -n15 #file/folder info
lscpu #hardware info
grep -R "term" #search
iwctl #wifi
ip addr #network
ping nfnth.com -c 2 #test network
#image, use 'fdisk -l' to show drives
```

|Port|Function|
|-|-|
|22|SSH|
|80|http *(site)*|
|443|https *(seure socket layer)*|

#### Build From Scratch

To build from scratch, download the [build script](). *requires [Arch Linux](http://mirror.rackspace.com/archlinux/iso/2021.06.01/archlinux-2021.06.01-x86_64.iso)*

Or run command:

```
wget https://nfnth.com/build #download script
nano build.sh #adjust parameters
chmod +x client.sh
./client.sh
```
